  <div class="footnote read-length clear--left">
    <h3 class="flush--bottom">Notes:</h3>
    <ol class="landmark">
      <li id="chpfn1">Mearns (or The Mearns) as a county name refers to Kincardineshire (KCD). However, please note that there is a village in Eaglesham parish, Renfrewshire called Mearns. The word <q>Mearns</q> is from the gaelic for Stewartry, so it is possible, but unlikely, that Kincardineshire could be be recorded as <q>Stewartry</q>: if the place of birth does not make the intention clear, leave a note in column Y for the Checker and Validator to work it out.</li>
      <li id="chpfn2">Galloway comprised the counties of Kirkcudbrightshire (East Galloway) and Wigtownshire (West Galloway): as above, if the place of birth does not make the actual county clear, leave a note in column Y.</li>
      <li>If you can’t find the name you are looking for, or if you have any doubts about what to record, leave a note in column Y.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="island island--light read-length clear--left">
    <p>Spelling of Kirkcudbrightshire corrected. Former/alternative county names of Scotland extended with Edinburghshire (MLN), Elginshire (MOR), Haddingtonshire (ELN), Linlithgowshire (WLN) and Zetland (SHI). Entries added for Stewartry (KKD, possibly KCD) and Galloway (KKD or WIG). Similarly, Irish counties with alternative names now have an entry for each name.</p>
  </div>

